data.contentText: Manage this baby according to the weight as below

metadata.text1:
Symmetrical small for gestational age infants (OFC in proportion with rest of body) should be evaluated for:
TORCH infections 
Chromosomal abnormalities
Anaemia
Foetal alcohol syndrome or other susbtance abuse

Asymmetrical growth restriction (sparing the head)
Evaluate for:
HYPOGLYCAEMIA- check blood sugar as a priority
Hypoxia
Polycythaemia

Do not discharge until feeds established.
metadata.text2:
May require cup feeds

Skin-skin & kangaroo care for thermoregulation

If the baby is feeding well with assistance, warm and not exhibiting any danger signs, the baby can stay their with mother

If the baby is not feeding well by breast, bottle, or cup or exhibiting any danger signs the baby should stay in neonatal unit
metadata.text3:
Needs admission to neonatal unit for close observation 

1500-2000g Trial cup feeds

Those <1500g should be fed by NGT and feeds advanced slowly as per the table

Check aspirates and refeed if <2ml.

Aspirates >2mL or greenish aspirates should prompt an examination of the baby

data.title: MANAGEMENT
